SIMPLE: seizure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seizure
<hw>Sei"zure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of seizing, or the state of being seized; sudden and violent grasp or
gripe; a taking into possession; <as>as, the <ex>seizure</ex> of a
thief, a property, a throne, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Retention within one's grasp or power; hold;
possession; ownership.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Make o'er thy honor by a deed of trust,⟦br⟧
And give me <qex>seizure</qex> of the mighty wealth.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is seized, or taken possession of; a
thing laid hold of, or possessed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sejeant</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sejant</ent>⟦br⟧
